summary: The Northeastern United States, also called the Northeast or East Coast, is one of four regions defined by the U.S. Census Bureau. It includes six New England states and three northern Mid-Atlantic states. The region borders Canada to the north, the Southern U.S. to the south, the Midwest to the west, and the Atlantic Ocean to the east. It's home to many large cities like Boston, New York, and Philadelphia, and is the most densely populated region in the U.S. with over 57 million people. Despite being the smallest region by area, it has a strong economy and high human development.
title: Northeastern United States
